Package interfaces

This package represents the interfaces displayed to the person using the ATM.

See: Description

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AccountInterface
    Class representing the account menu that will be displayed in the interface for users to manage their accounts.
    BankManagerInterface
    A class representing the bank manager menu that will be displayed in the interface for bank managers to perform the required tasks: set date, create user, create account, check alerts, restock machine, undo transactions for users, shut down the system.
    BrokerInterface
    Class representing the broker menu that will be displayed in the interface for broker to be able to buy and sell mutual funds for the ATM.
    GeneralInterfaceMethods
    A class that has methods that can be implemented in multiple classes, such as AccountInterface, BankManagerInterface and TransactionInterface.
    Interface
    Main interface class that whoever is running the ATM will see.
    InvestmentInterface
    Class for the investments interface.
    SubscriptionInterface
    Class for subscription interface which manages all subscriptions for a user.
    TransactionInterface
    Class for the transaction interface that the user will see.
    UpdateProfileInterface
    Class for updating profile interface for the user.
    UserInterface
    A class for the what the user will be able see when they log in to ATM.

Package interfaces Description

This package represents the interfaces displayed to the person using the ATM.
